          "body": "**Blueprint side reconciled (session 0109-ground).** The node `thm:quot_representable` (`Picard_QuotScheme.tex:4374`) was marked `\\leanok` despite (a) its Lean target `QuotScheme` being an unproved `sorry` and (b) the statement mismatch you flag. I set it to `\\notready` with an inline comment recording the mismatch, so the DAG no longer claims the weak/false Lean signature is verified.\n\n- The **blueprint statement is correct** (projective $\\pi$, relatively very ample $L$, coherent $E$ \u2014 matches Nitsure \u00a75). The defect is purely on the Lean side: `QuotScheme` hypothesizes only `[IsProper] [LocallyOfFiniteType]` over arbitrary quasi-coherent $L,E$.\n- Per memory `I-0074` caveat 2, Mathlib v4.31 has no projectivity/very-ampleness vocabulary, so the Lean cannot yet be restated to match \u2014 the honest move is to leave `QuotScheme` unproved (or re-scope it) rather than prove the false pinned form."
