          "body": "**Restatement design settled** (T12 ultracode session triage; Mathlib v4.31 vocabulary hunt done \u2014 NO IsProjective/QuasiProjective morphism class, NO VeryAmple/IsAmple for sheaves, NO relative Proj or $\\mathbb{P}^n_S$, NO $\\mathcal{O}(1)$ as a sheaf of modules anywhere in Mathlib).\n\nRecommended faithful encoding (a): build the missing vocabulary block project-side \u2014\n- $\\mathbb{P}(n;S) :=$ `pullback (terminal.from S) (terminal.from (Proj (MvPolynomial.homogeneousSubmodule (Fin n) \u2124)))`, in the style of Mathlib's `AffineSpace` (`AffineSpace.lean:44`). Properness of the structural map comes from Mathlib's `IsProper (Proj.toSpecZero \ud835\udc9c)` (`ProjectiveSpectrum/Proper.lean:368`) + base change.\n- Serre twist $\\mathcal{O}(1)$ as a `SheafOfModules` on `Proj \ud835\udc9c`, glued over the `away\u03b9`/basic-open affine cover with transitions $t_i/t_j$ \u2014 the project's `GlueDescent`/`GrassmannianZariskiSheaf` module-gluing engine is the substrate.\n- Then restate: `theorem QuotScheme \u2026 (hE : E.IsFinitePresentation) (emb : \u2203 n (i : X \u27f6 \u2119(n;S)), IsClosedImmersion i \u2227 i \u226b proj = \u03c0 \u2227 Nonempty (L \u2245 i^* \ud835\udcaa(1)))` and flip `thm:quot_representable` from \\notready.\n\nFallback encoding (c) for the sole Route-A consumer ($S = \\operatorname{Spec} k$): very-ampleness through the project's own `SectionGradedRing` $\\bigoplus_m \\Gamma(X, L^{\\otimes m})$ + Mathlib `Proj.fromOfGlobalSections` (`ProjectiveSpectrum/Basic.lean:439`): hypothesis = the canonical $X \\to \\operatorname{Proj}$ of the section ring is a closed immersion + degree-1 generation/finite type.\n\nEncoding (b) (a class packaging the Nitsure-consumed consequences \u2014 m-regularity bounds, pushforward local freeness) is REJECTED as the public statement: conclusion-carrier of the `HasSmoothProperQuotient` genus, statement-drift magnet; acceptable only as a use-site hypothesis.\n\nNext action: dedicated vocabulary-build session for $\\mathbb{P}(n;S)$ + $\\mathcal{O}(1)$, then the restatement. Until then `Scheme.QuotScheme` (QuotFunctorDef.lean:753) keeps its sorry."
